    <item>
      <title>Shortcodes</title>
      <link>https://juzhyo.github.io/alisont/it/catalogue/shortcodes/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://juzhyo.github.io/alisont/it/catalogue/shortcodes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In addition to all the &lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/content-management/shortcodes/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;default Hugo shortcodes&lt;/a&gt;, Blowfish adds a few extras for additional functionality.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Alert&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;alert&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#alert&#34; aria-label=&#34;Ancora&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;alert&lt;/code&gt; outputs its contents as a stylised message box within your article. It&amp;rsquo;s useful for drawing attention to important information that you don&amp;rsquo;t want the reader to miss.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://juzhyo.github.io/alisont/catalogue/shortcodes/featured.svg" />
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Shortcodes</title>
      <link>https://juzhyo.github.io/alisont/it/docs/shortcodes/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://juzhyo.github.io/alisont/it/docs/shortcodes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In addition to all the &lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/content-management/shortcodes/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;default Hugo shortcodes&lt;/a&gt;, Blowfish adds a few extras for additional functionality.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Alert&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;alert&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#alert&#34; aria-label=&#34;Ancora&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;alert&lt;/code&gt; outputs its contents as a stylised message box within your article. It&amp;rsquo;s useful for drawing attention to important information that you don&amp;rsquo;t want the reader to miss.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://juzhyo.github.io/alisont/docs/shortcodes/featured.svg" />
    </item>
    
